This paper discusses the use of natural language processing and speech signal processing for objective assessments of speech and language in the context of cognitive and thought disorders. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing. The paper also mentions the use of machine learning and artificial intelligence, which suggests cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as another likely category. The paper also discusses the use of signal processing techniques, which suggests cs.SD (Sound) as a possible category. Additionally, the paper discusses the clinical application of these techniques, which suggests cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) as another possible category. Finally, the paper discusses the advantages and disadvantages of different features, which suggests cs.LG (Learning) as a possible category.
